parameters: \nc<>Leave it to me today... P-Pufu, Puhahaha!
\nc<>Killing... I guess I really am a bad child after all...

\nc<>Ahem, ahem! Please don't get too down, senpai. It was just
bad luck with the weather.

\nc<>And besides, the last movie was pretty interesting, wasn't
it?

\nc<>Recent superhero movies are flashy and good, aren't they?
It's a feast for the eyes.

\nc<>It's a little disappointing that the story becomes neglected
as a result.

\nc<>Is that so? I think the protagonist's struggles and
awakening as a hero were well portrayed.

\nc<>As for the protagonist, that's true, but the villain's
appearances were extremely few, weren't they?

\nc<>There was no explanation as to why they became a villain or
what they wanted, they just seemed to be defeated because
they did bad things.

\nc<>I don't think it's because they're bad people that they
become villains, but rather because they're villains that
they do bad things. I don't think that's very heroic at
all.

\nc<>(Hmm... that might be true. I certainly never thought about
the circumstances on the villain's side.)

\nc<>(Can we call it being a hero) (to relentlessly corner
someone without trying to understand them?)
\nc<>...I'm the same as the villain, aren't I?

\nc<>Look, Senpai is so cute, right? They're completely different
from those creepy villains.

\nc<>It's not a satisfying answer. There are also cute ones like
Lilith, you know.

\nc<>Well, joking aside, no matter the reason, it doesn't mean
that doing bad things is justified.
\nc<>I don't think you need to worry too much.

\nc<>Well, anyway, we're still in the middle of our date,
right?
\nc<>Since the dessert has finally arrived, Senpai, ahh~
\nc<>I obtained the memory R3: Chaotic Date.
